# Phase 2: Capture Engine Implementation Walkthrough

## New Components

### [NetworkCapture.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/capture/NetworkCapture.ts)
This new class encapsulates the network interception logic previously found in [background/index.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts).
- **Features**:
  - [start()](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/capture/NetworkCapture.ts#21-42) / [stop()](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/capture/NetworkCapture.ts#43-56) lifecycle methods.
  - Captures `webRequest.onSendHeaders` and `webRequest.onResponseStarted`.
  - Implements resource size filtering (`minFileSize`, `maxFileSize`).
  - Implements URL filtering (Blacklist/Whitelist/Regex).
  - Implements MIME type and extension detection.

### [mimeTypes.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/constants/mimeTypes.ts)
Centralized definition of media extensions and MIME types.

### [media.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/utils/media.ts)
Refactored utility functions for detecting resource types (`video`, `audio`, etc.) and stream types (`hls`, `dash`, etc.).

## Refactoring

### [background/index.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts)
- Removed inline `webRequest` logic.
- Now initializes and starts the [NetworkCapture](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/capture/NetworkCapture.ts#11-247) engine.
- Cleaner entry point, focused on lifecycle and messaging.

